Preheat your oven to 200°C. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Put it in a #mixing bowl{} with the @olive oil{2%tbsp}, @ground cumin{0.75%tsp} and a good squeeze of @lemon{1/2}. Add the @British chicken thighs{4}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and toss to coat thoroughly, then set aside to marinate. Make sure you wash your hands after handling raw chicken!

Chop the @red potato{1} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel) and pop on a lined #baking tray{}. Drizzle over a glug of oil. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and sprinkle on the @smoked paprika{1.5%tsp}. Toss to coat, then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until slightly crispy, ~{30%minutes}. Give the #tray{} a shake halfway through.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @red chilli{1/4}(halved lengthways, deseeded, finely chopped). Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat. Add the garlic, remaining @ground cumin{0.75%tsp} and the chilli (use less if you don't like heat). Cook for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the @tomato passata{1%cup}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, stir, bring to a simmer and cook on low heat for about ~{7%minutes}.

While the sauce cooks, lay the chicken on another lined baking tray and roast on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{20-25%minutes}. TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, remove the top and bottom from the @courgette{1}. Slice into 1cm thick rounds. Put a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil) and leave it for a couple of mins to get hot. Lay in the courgette slices and cook until slightly charred, ~{4-5%minutes} on each side. TIP: Do this in batches if necessary to avoid overcrowding the pan. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then remove from the heat.

When the potato and chicken are ready, remove them from your oven. Pop the potato on your plates and spoon over some of the bravas sauce. Add the cumin roast chicken and a few of the charred courgettes. Buen provecho!

> Holidays are over but today's recipe will transport you to Spain. Although it was actually inspired by Mimi's visit to a tapas restaurant in Dundee! Patatas bravas is the quintessential tapas dish, available all over Spain. Not everyone loves the casual, sharing business of tapas so we've given you plenty for a portion each alongside some delicious cumin roast chicken!